  "sourceFile": "Waste_notes/sweetthames_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Sweet\n        Thames ...</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>V. Spenser, <i>Prothalamion</i>. [Eliot's note]\n        Eliot's line is the refrain from Spenser's marriage song,\n        which is also set by the Thames in London - but a very\n        different Thames from the modern littered river (NA). </p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Spenser, <em>Prothalamion</em></td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Sweet Thames ... V. Spenser, Prothalamion . [Eliot's note] Eliot's line is the refrain from Spenser's marriage song, which is also set by the Thames in London - but a very different Thames from the modern littered river (NA). reference topics Spenser, Prothalamion back to \"The Waste Land\"",
